No problem, I get what you're saying. I do understand what you mean by the mythos being confusing to those who aren't familiar with it, though personally I find that when I read an SCP that relates to another it makes me want to dive into the universe even more to get the whole story; the first thing that comes to my mind is the Herman Fuller SCPs, which have been another one of my big inspirations for writing around here. (That being said, most of those are independent of each other overall, with individual experiences of performers/items, rather than an interconnected story.)







